<sect1 id="fantasdic-introduction">
<title>Introduction</title>

<para><application>&app;</application> is a dictionary application. It enables
to look up words in various dictionary sources.
</para>

</sect1>

<sect1 id="fantasdic-getting-started">
<title>Getting Started</title>

<para>You can start <application>&app;</application> in the following
ways:</para>

<variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
        <term><guimenu>Applications</guimenu> menu</term>
        <listitem>
            <para>Choose
                <menuchoice><guisubmenu>Accessories</guisubmenu>
                            <guimenuitem>Fantasdic</guimenuitem>
                </menuchoice>.
            </para>
        </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
        <term>Command line</term>
        <listitem>
            <para>Execute the following command:
                <command>fantasdic</command></para>
        </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
</variablelist>

<para>Once started, the <application>&app;</application> window is
    displayed:</para>

<figure id="fantasdic-fig">
    <title>&app; Window</title>
    <screenshot>
        <mediaobject>
            <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="figures/fantasdic.png" format="PNG"/>
            </imageobject>
            <textobject><phrase>Shows &app; main window.</phrase></textobject>
        </mediaobject>
    </screenshot>
</figure>
</sect1>


<sect1 id="fantasdic-usage">
<title>Usage</title>

<sect2 id="fantasdic-looking-up-a-word">
<title>Looking up a word</title>

<para>To look up a word, type it into the <guilabel>entry field</guilabel>
and press <keycap>Enter</keycap>. It is possible to change the match strategy
by using the <guilabel>left combo box</guilabel> and the dictionary used to look
up words by using the <guilabel>right combo
box</guilabel>.

<tip><para>Dictionaries can be added and changed at any time in the preferences.
Available match strategies depend on the dictionary selected.</para></tip>
</para>

<para>If some definition for the word is found, it will appear inside the main
window area:</para>

<figure id="fantasdic-dictionary-lookup-fig">
    <title>&app; Window</title>
    <screenshot>
        <mediaobject>
            <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="figures/fantasdic-search.png"
                           format="PNG"/>
            </imageobject>
            <textobject><phrase>Shows a definition inside the &app; main
                    window.</phrase></textobject>
        </mediaobject>
    </screenshot>
</figure>

<para>Otherwise, an error dialog will appear, with a message explaining the     
 nature of the error.</para>

</sect2>

<sect2 id="fantasdic-saving-results">
    <title>Saving results</title>
    
    <para>To save the results of a look up, choose
<menuchoice><guimenu>Fantasdic</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Save</guimenuitem></menuchoice >. Enter a name for the file in the
<guilabel>Save</guilabel> dialog, then click <guibutton>Save</guibutton>.</para>
    
</sect2>

<sect2 id="fantasdic-printing-results">
    <title>Printing results</title>
    
    <para>To print the results of a look up, choose
<menuchoice><guimenu>Fantasdic</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Print</guimenuitem></menuchoice>.</para>
    
<para>Inside the <guilabel>Print</guilabel> dialog, select the
printer to use, the paper format, the number of copies.</para>

<para>To see a preview of what will be printed, click
<guibutton>Preview</guibutton>.</para>
    
</sect2>

<sect2 id="fantasdic-finding-text">
    <title>Finding text</title>
    
    <figure id="fantasdic-find-fig">
        <title>&app; Window</title>
        <screenshot>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="figures/fantasdic-find-text.png"
                               format="PNG"/>
                </imageobject>
                <textobject><phrase>Shows the &app; Find pane inside the main
                        window.</phrase></textobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </screenshot>
    </figure>    
    
    <para>To find text inside the results of a look up, perform the following
        steps:</para>
    
    <orderedlist>
        <listitem><para>Choose <menuchoice> <guimenu>Edit</guimenu>
        <guimenuitem>Find</guimenuitem> </menuchoice> to display the
        <guilabel>Find</guilabel> pane.</para></listitem>
        <listitem><para>Type the text to find inside the
                <guilabel>Search</guilabel> entry.</para></listitem>
        <listitem><para>To find the next occurrence of the text, click
        <guibutton>Next</guibutton>.
        To find the previous occurrence of the text, click
        <guibutton>Previous</guibutton>.</para></listitem>
      </orderedlist>

    <para>The <guilabel>find pane</guilabel> can be quickly closed by pressing
        <keycap>Escape</keycap>.</para>
  
</sect2>

<sect2 id="fantasdic-scanning-clipboard">
    <title>Scanning the clipboard</title>
    
    <para>When the <guimenuitem>Scan clipboard</guimenuitem> option is
        enabled, words copied to the clipboard are automatically looked
        up by Fantasdic. To enable this option, choose
        <menuchoice><guimenu>Edit</guimenu>
        <guimenuitem>Scan clipboard</guimenuitem></menuchoice>.</para>

</sect2>

<sect2 id="fantasdic-system-tray">
    <title>System tray</title>
    
    <para>Optionally, Fantasdic can stay in the system tray. To
quickly close Fantasdic, press <keycap>Escape</keycap>. To bring
Fantasdic back, click on the <guiicon>Fantasdic icon</guiicon>.</para>

    <figure id="fantasdic-system-tray-fig">
        <title>Fantasdic in the system tray</title>
        <screenshot>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="figures/fantasdic-system-tray.png"
                            format="PNG"/>
                </imageobject>
                <textobject><phrase>Shows Fantasdic in
                        the system tray.</phrase></textobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </screenshot>
    </figure>    
    
</sect2>

</sect1>

<sect1 id="fantasdic-preferences">
<title>Preferences</title>

<para>To change the application preferences, choose
<menuchoice><guimenu>Edit</guimenu><guimenuitem>Preferences</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>.</para>

<sect2 id="fantasdic-preferences-dictionaries">
    <title>Dictionaries</title>

    <figure id="fantasdic-preferences-dictionaries-fig">
        <title>Dictionaries tab</title>
        <screenshot>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata
                        fileref="figures/fantasdic-preferences-dictionaries.png"
                        format="PNG"/>
                </imageobject>
                <textobject><phrase>Shows the Dictionaries
                tab</phrase></textobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </screenshot>
    </figure>    
    
    <para>To add a dictionary, choose <guibutton>Add</guibutton>.</para>

    <para>To change an existing dictionary, select the desired dictionary
    and choose <guibutton>Properties</guibutton>. To remove an existing
    dictionary, choose <guibutton>Remove</guibutton>.</para>

    <warning><para>If a dictionary is removed, it will be permanently
    deleted from the list of available dictionaries.</para></warning>

    <para>For further details, see the <link   
    linkend="fantasdic-dictionaries">dictionaries section</link>.</para>

</sect2>

